==Assembly==
[[File:Fat Man Detonation.png|thumb|right|Fat Man's detonation method]]
[[File:Fat Man Assembly Tinian 1945.jpg|thumb|right|Fat Man's "physics package" nuclear device about to be encased]]
[[File:Fat Man Assembled Tinian 1945.jpg|thumb|right|Fat Man on its transport carriage, with liquid asphalt sealant applied over the casing's seams]]
[[File:Atomic Bomb Pits - Tinian - panoramio (3).jpg|thumb|right|Preserved Tinian "bomb pit #2", where Fat Man was loaded aboard ''Bockscar'']]

The [[plutonium pit]]{{sfn|Coster-Mullen|2012|p=52}} was {{convert|3.62|in|mm|adj=on}} in diameter and contained an "Urchin" [[modulated neutron initiator]] that was {{convert|0.8|in|mm|adj=on}} in diameter. The [[depleted uranium]] [[neutron reflector|tamper]] was a {{convert|8.75|in|mm|adj=on}} diameter sphere, surrounded by a {{convert|0.125|in|mm|adj=on}} thick shell of boron-impregnated plastic. The plastic shell had a {{convert|5|in|mm|adj=on}} diameter cylindrical hole running through it, like the hole in a cored apple, in order to allow insertion of the pit as late as possible. The missing tamper cylinder containing the pit could be slipped in through a hole in the surrounding {{convert|18.5|in|mm|adj=on}} diameter aluminum pusher.{{sfn|Coster-Mullen|2012|p=186}} The pit was warm to touch, emitting 2.4 W/kg-Pu, about 15 W for the {{convert|6.19|kg}} core.{{sfn|Coster-Mullen|2012|p=49}}

The explosion symmetrically compressed the plutonium to twice its normal density before the "Urchin" added [[free neutron]]s to initiate a [[nuclear fission|fission]] [[nuclear chain reaction|chain reaction]].{{sfn|Coster-Mullen|2012|p=45}}

